Legalization of Hanchongryon called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- 47 members of the "National Assembly" from ruling and opposition parties of South Korea issued a joint statement on April 18 demanding the legalization of the South Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon), the release of prisoners of conscience and the lifting of search for wanted political offenders, according to MBC of South Korea.
 Since the security authorities listed Hanchongryon as an "enemy-benefiting organization" in 1997, hundreds of students have annually suffered as wanted political offenders, the statement said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "government" and society should pave the way for lifting the "enemy-benefiting" label from Hanchongryon and opening a charter for the future-oriented movement of students. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To this end, the "government" should examine the release of prisoners of conscience and the lifting of search for wanted political offenders and move to declare the student movement legal.

April 19 declaration issued in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The group of chairmen of General Student Councils of 64 Universities of South Korea including Korea University, Kyunghee University, Duksung Women's University and Sogang University held a press conference at Dongguk University on April 19 and issued an "April 19 Declaration" demanding an immediate stop to the U.S. Iraqi war and the withdrawal of the decision on troop dispatch to it, Yonhap News from Seoul said.
 Humankind is so strongly opposed to the U.S. war because it is an unjust war of genocide and a reckless war to hold world supremacy by dint of the "policy of strength", the declaration said, and noted: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will oppose the decision of the "government" and the "National Assembly" to dispatch troops, going against the people's will, and struggle till the day it is cancelled so that young people in this land are not hurled into that war of genocide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration stressed that they would make June 13 when a memorial service will be held one year after schoolgirls Mi Son and Hyo Sun were brutally killed by a U.S. armored car a "day of student action" to encourage 3 million students to rise up in a campaign against the U.S. war which will claim lives of so many young people like the schoolgirls.

U.S. attempt to stifle DPRK bound to go bust 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The U.S. is getting frantic with its nuclear racket to isolate and stifle the DPRK, raising a hue and cry over its "nuclear issue" on the international arena.
 Accusing the U.S. imperialists of aggravating the situation on the Korean Peninsula under the pretext of the "nuclear issue," Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article says: They staged foal eagle and reception, staging, onward movement and integration joint military exercises together with the South Korean army in all areas of the south for over one month with various types of means for nuclear attack and ultra-modern military hardware involved. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush administration listed the DPRK as part of an "axis of evil" and the target of its preemptive nuclear attack. And it has become desperate in its nuclear racket against the DPRK and moves to provoke a new war under the pretext of its "nuclear issue". All this is aimed at executing its policy of aggression toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the U.S. imperialists' attempt to stifle the DPRK has gone beyond the danger line, the process of peace and reconciliation on the Korean Peninsula has been blocked and the danger of a nuclear war is increasing hour by hour. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' attempt to stifle the DPRK is a sheer daydream. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK is the heroic army and people who inflicted a bitter defeat upon the U.S. imperialists who boasted of being the "strongest in the world". The U.S. imperialists should draw a lesson from its defeat in the past Korean war they started against the young DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. ignites a nuclear war in Korea, our revolutionary armed forces will mercilessly wipe out the aggressors and put a final end to the confrontation with the U.S.

U.S. argument about "human rights situation" rejected 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The United States is taking issue with the DPRK over the "human rights issue" to attain its sinister aims, but it is as foolish an act as trying to sweep the sea with a broom, says Rodong Sinmun today in a commentary.
 The U.S. is a graveyard of human rights where the rich get richer and the poor poorer and many people are not granted even an elementary right to existence. It is monstrous that such country talks about the "human rights situation" in the DPRK, the news analyst says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What the U.S. seeks in raising the "human rights issue" as well as the "nuclear issue" is to cripple the Korean people's trust in their socialist system and violate the DPRK's sovereignty while impairing its international prestige and increasing the international pressure upon it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Human rights mean national rights and sovereignty is the most vivid manifestation of human rights. This is the truth evidenced by the historical practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nothing can break the Korean people's confidence in the DPRK and its socialist system. steadfast is the singlehearted unity of the leader, the party and the masses in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though the U.S. persistently plays the old tune about "human rights", nobody pays attention to it as it will only reveal more faults of the U.S. as a violator of human rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is well advised not to engage itself in such vain efforts.

43rd anniversary of April Popular Uprising commemorated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Meetings and demonstrations to honour the memory of forerunners were held in different parts of South Korea on April 19 on the occasion of the April Popular Uprising, according to Yonhap News from Seoul. 
 A ceremony for commemorating the April Popular Uprising took place at the cemetery of April 19 martyrs in Seoul with the attendance of more than 1,000 members of organizations concerning the uprising, citizens and students. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony chairman of the society of the wounded of the April 19 revolution Kang Jae Sik made a report on the then uprising, which was followed by a memorial poem recitation, April 19 singing in unison, photo exhibition and musical concert to the memory of forerunners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the national alliance for democracy and reunification and other public organizations held a commemoration meeting at the same place. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over 400 members of the solidarity for implementing the south-north joint declaration made the "April 19 street march for the defence of peace against U.S. and war" from the square of the Seoul railway station to the Thapgol park on the same day, shouting slogans "against the U.S. war in the Korean Peninsula," "withdrawal of the U.S. troops, murderer of school girls" and so on.

Foundations of Songun politics provided by Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) --The foundations of the Songun politics pursued by the Workers' Party of Korea were laid by President Kim Il Sung.
 He, who started the revolutionary activities in his early years, formulated the idea that the only choice for the liberation of the country from the Japanese imperialists' rule was to wage an armed struggle. He formed an anti-Japanese guerrilla army and accomplished the historical cause of national liberation through the armed struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the Korean war and in the period of the peaceful construction, he always attached great importance to the military, regarding it as the most important thing in the state affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his leadership the Korean people have emerged victorious in the long-standing political and military confrontation with the U.S. imperialists and successfully built the socialist society with the backing of a strong military power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For military buildup he advanced policies of training the whole army into a cadre army, modernizing the whole army, arming the entire people and turning the whole country into a fortress and made inspection tours of army units for their implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also put forward a policy of carrying on the economic construction in parallel with military buildup so that the Korean people could defend the country by themselves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He provided conditions for the continuity of the Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean revolution has triumphantly advanced in the face of the imperialists' challenges, as leader Kim Jong Il has increased the nation's defence capacity with the Songun politics.

New potato processing method developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The grain processing institute of the branch academy of light industrial science has developed a new method of potato food processing.
 The method makes it possible to produce riced potato, dried potato noodle, potato bread, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The streamlined system consists of peeling, slicing, wring, mixture of potato flour with other kinds of flour, and packing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new method increases the actual extraction rate up to 90 percent by using most of nutritive elements such as protein, vitamin and mineral matter contained in potato. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The institute has also developed a method of preventing potato discoloration with the help of enzyme, different from the chemical method using sulphurous acid, hydrochloric acid, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
And it has lifted the proportion of potato up to 50 percent in the production of potato bread.

Jo Myong Rok's sojourn in Beijing
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Beijing, April 21 (KCNA) -- A ceremony took place in the plaza in front of the August 1 Building here today to welcome Jo Myong Rok, first vice-chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, visiting China.
 Present at the welcome ceremony were Jo Myong Rok and general Pak Jae Gyong and col. gen. Pak Sung Won of the Korean People's Army, DPRK Ambassador Choe Jin Su and other suite members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were col. gen. Guo Boxiong, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission of the People's Republic of China and vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission of the Communist Party of China, col. gen. Xu Caihou, director of the general political department of the Chinese People's Liberation Army who is member of the CPC Central Military Commission and concurrently member of the PRC Central Military Commission, col. gen. Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the CPLA general staff, and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day, Jo Myong Rok met with Guo Boxiong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Guo said that China and the DPRK are friendly neighbors bordering on the same mountain and river and their traditional friendship has a long history. The Sino-Korean friendship had been cultivated and developed by Chairman Mao Zedong, Premier Zhou Enlai, Deng Xiaoping and President Kim Il Sung and other veteran revolutionaries of the two countries, and it is a precious heritage they left for us, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the new historical time, the bilateral friendship is further developing under the care of Chairman Jiang Zemin and General Secretary kim jong il, he said, expressing belief that the friendly relations between the two parties, governments and armies of china and the DPRK will be put on a higher stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He hoped that the Korean people and army would make greater success in the state building, the improvement of the standard of people's living and the modernization of the army under the correct guidance of Kim Jong Il and the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jo also met and had a friendly talk with col. gen. Cao Gangchuan, state councillor and minister of defence who is vice-chairman of the CPC Central Military Commission and concurrently vice-chairman of the PRC Central Military Commission.

Koreans called upon to turn out for national reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The south headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification released a statement on April 18 on the occasion of the 55th anniversary of the joint conference of representatives of political parties and public organizations in South and North Korea.
 The joint conference demonstrated to the world that the Koreans can certainly achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country if they unite, irrespective of ideology, system and religious belief, and the Korean nation is a dignified nation with wisdom and ability to settle its issue by itself, the statement noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation is responsible for achieving national reunification and independent and peaceful reunification would be unthinkable without the unity of the south and the north and great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement called on all Koreans to intensify the struggle, deeply aware that the great national unity is a shortcut to national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement appealed to the 70 million Koreans to vigorously turn out on the road of patriotism to bring earlier the independent and peaceful reunification of the country by fully realizing the national cooperation between the south and the north in the same spirit of great national unity as was displayed during the April joint conference and thoroughly implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration, a landmark of national reunification.
